Dialogue: 10,0:01:11.69,0:01:18.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The tragic war fought between Japan and the US\N for dominance over Asia and the Pacific
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.05,0:01:21.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,ended with the unconditional surrender of Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:21.28,0:01:22.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:23.90,0:01:29.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This story begins two years and four months prior,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:29.36,0:01:35.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,when a certain admiral is shot down from the skies\Nabove the island of Bougainville in the South Pacific.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.68,0:01:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,More hostiles at 6 o'clock!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:01.92,0:02:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep them off our backs, escort units... {直掩機}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.26,0:02:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.00,0:02:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Left engine is out!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.80,0:02:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there fire?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.10,0:02:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, just smoke!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.94,0:02:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:22.26,0:02:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Left engine's internal pressure is falling!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.65,0:02:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm raising the nose!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.70,0:02:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.65,0:02:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.20,0:03:08.36,Thought,,0,0,0,,I unmistakably died back then at Bougainville.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:10.12,0:03:12.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,But when I woke up,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.39,0:03:20.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was aboard the cruiser Nisshin, amidst the Battle of Tsushima, thirty-eight years in the past...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.17,0:03:28.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,And so, I found myself \Nreliving the exact same life...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:28.04,0:03:31.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,No, to be more precise,\Nit could hardly be called the exact same.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.81,0:03:36.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,In my previous life, I had lost two fingers\Nas a result of an injury aboard the Nisshin.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.95,0:03:40.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,On top of that, I still bear my old name, Takano,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.32,0:03:42.87,Thought,,0,0,0,,having never taken Yamamoto, the name \Nof my adoptive family. {In 1916, Isoroku was adopted into the Yamamoto family (another family of former Nagaoka samurai) and took the Yamamoto name. It was a common practice for samurai families lacking sons to adopt suitable young men in this fashion to carry on the family name, the rank, and the income that went with it.}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:42.87,0:03:45.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,Even the kanji for Showa is different. {not sure what's that mio, but here we see 照和 (terukazu) instead of 昭和 (shouwa); however, later in the show narrator still uses the normal showa years; we'll see}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.84,0:03:48.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,I have reincarnated into this world.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.00,0:03:51.33,Thought,,0,0,0,,However, just as my previous world,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.33,0:03:54.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,this world is walking down the path of ruin.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.58,0:03:58.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must stop the tragedy from my past life\Nfrom repeating at all costs.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.42,0:04:04.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,There is hardly any time left \Nuntil war breaks out on the 8th of December.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.31,0:04:05.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,I must make haste.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.01,0:04:10.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As the prelude to the Pacific War grew stronger with each passing day,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.20,0:04:15.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Takano Isoroku had set a certain plan in motion. \NAnd that plan was...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.66,0:04:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be late tonight. \NYou go on without me.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.83,0:04:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.23,0:04:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, my lord.\NEveryone has gathered already.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.80,0:04:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for having us.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.11,0:04:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Takano has arrived.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.68,0:04:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for being late.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.92,0:04:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.29,0:04:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We all arrived just now as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.24,0:04:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,, I see. Ma'am, leave the drinks for later.\NI'll call you when we're done.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.23,0:04:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.50,0:05:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, the situation \Nhas at last come to a head.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.72,0:05:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, has the Imperial Army \Ntried something again?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.17,0:05:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. In fact, some Army fools were lying in ambush again \Nin front of my office just this morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.98,0:05:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they're the pro-war faction, \Nand they're on it again.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.95,0:05:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So riled up they wouldn't even listen to reason.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.75,0:05:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, it is not only the Imperial Army \Nthat is currently poised to strike.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:20.82,0:05:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There are also those within our own Navy.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.66,0:05:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention right-wingers,\Nreservists, even provincial assemblymen...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.58,0:05:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them are fervently calling\Nfor a strike at the US and UK.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.93,0:05:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Like broken records, the lot of them!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.60,0:05:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even as we speak, this country is being devoured \Nby the monster of nationalism.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.27,0:05:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Many are losing touch with reality.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.81,0:05:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If this goes on...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.00,0:05:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Will war break out, after all?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.18,0:05:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt.\NThere's no stopping it now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.16,0:05:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! But that means...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.05,0:05:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, war will surely break out \Nby early December next year.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.75,0:05:59.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This assembly, hosted by Takano,\Nhad been named the Deep Blue Society.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.20,0:06:03.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Many of the members were people who had also \Nbeen reincarnated from the previous world
Dialogue: 10,0:06:03.20,0:06:04.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and now enjoyed prosperous lives,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.90,0:06:09.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but there were also technical officers, \Ncivilian engineers, and a few business people.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.78,0:06:15.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Their research was known as Project 1208. {referring to the order of attack on pearl harbor on december 8th}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.80,0:06:23.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In other words, they were looking into a way to prevent the tragic history of the Pacific War from occurring.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.98,0:06:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with oil, another large issue \Nthat we must cover
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.85,0:06:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is radar technology, \Ncommunications, and encryption...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.24,0:06:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm, regarding that, I have a report to present.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.20,0:06:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Are our prospects looking well?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.70,0:06:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thanks to the talents \Nof our very own Kubo Seichiro here. {dunno if he has any historical prototype}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:41.06,0:06:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, regarding communications, we are currently prototyping a system that does not use vacuum tubes.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.07,0:06:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, we are conducting prototype research \Non a special computer that uses this method.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.28,0:06:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When that is completed, not only will our codes \Nbe safe from enemy decryption,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.98,0:07:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we will also be capable of deciphering any \Nof the enemy's codes, no matter how complex.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.42,0:07:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's magnificent!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.72,0:07:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wars fought from here on out\Nwill be wars of intelligence, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.28,0:07:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed. We expect great things.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.79,0:07:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A high-speed computer is also indispensable \Nfor plotting the G7 torpedo, which I am currently studying. {probably https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G7e_torpedo ? not sure what it has to do with tactics, maybe it's actually some other, obscure military word}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.34,0:07:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.38,0:07:18.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Takano left the meeting early.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:18.04,0:07:21.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The fatigue from several consecutive days \Nof hard work was catching up to him.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.56,0:07:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of the rest, Ma'am.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.10,0:07:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.98,0:07:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral Takano?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.58,0:07:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.92,0:07:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I help you?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:38.02,0:07:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is divine punishment!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.21,0:07:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.17,0:07:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You accursed fool!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.58,0:07:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still not understand\Nwhat this will lead to?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.88,0:07:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.64,0:08:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.72,0:08:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.75,0:08:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, are you injured?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.39,0:08:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:08.82,0:08:10.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,M-My fingers...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.62,0:08:12.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,History is repeating after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.96,0:08:12.43,Top,,0,0,0,,Ma'am, call a doctor! Quickly!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.43,0:08:13.19,Top,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.19,0:08:16.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, Takano's injuries\Nweren't fatal, and instead,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.50,0:08:21.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Imperial Army was made to listen to reason \Nfor the time being, as a result of this incident. {lit: irrational (line of) argument was suppressed}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.77,0:08:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, one day...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.10,0:08:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? What? From Lord Otaka?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.88,0:08:32.28,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,In his call, Lieutenant General Otaka Yasaburo
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.88,0:08:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Put him through. Hello?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.28,0:08:35.65,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,requested for them to meet privately, \Naway from prying eyes and ears. {rikugun chuujou is specifically "lieutenant general (army)​" - not sure how that works if https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jisabur%C5%8D_Ozawa was a navy officer irl}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.65,0:08:39.29,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,Wondering what this could be about, \Nbut realizing that Otaka
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.29,0:08:43.49,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,was unusually shrewd for an army officer, \NTakano readily agreed to meet with him.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.12,0:08:50.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,To keep it from drawing attention, he set \Nthe meeting up at a small restaurant in Kagurazaka. {https://maps.app.goo.gl/rcPT3y46ZAgVqJcK6}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.50,0:08:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Your company has arrived.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.07,0:08:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.04,0:08:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Please excuse me.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.10,0:08:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy yourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.82,0:09:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for joining me.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.95,0:09:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, have a seat.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:07.56,0:09:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Otaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:09.95,0:09:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Takano.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.09,0:09:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was greatly influenced by your work \Nas Yamamoto in my previous life.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.34,0:09:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so you're one of us too?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.10,0:09:24.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In an instant, they saw through to\None another's true identities.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.60,0:09:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,From observing your everyday demeanor,\NI've realized that we're kindred spirits.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.27,0:09:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Word of the Deep Blue Society \Nhas also reached my ears.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.41,0:09:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You have me at a loss.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:34.81,0:09:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I have formed a group \Nwith similar aspirations, called the Cool Breeze Society. {assuming this seifuu is "breath of fresh air; cool (refreshing) breeze"}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.26,0:09:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.61,0:09:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.88,0:09:48.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was here that two fellow men who had experienced the same past,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.19,0:09:52.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,having realized that their evaluations of current situation and future prospects perfectly aligned,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.64,0:09:54.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,decided to form a partnership.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.03,0:09:56.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, what truly caught Takano's attention
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.61,0:09:59.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was this opinion held by Otaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.10,0:10:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The point is, it is not about \Nhow we win, but how we lose.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.94,0:10:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, our nation achieved \Nseveral victories even in our past lives.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.11,0:10:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But the disparity in power {between us and the US }\Nwas too great to overcome.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.95,0:10:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We will undoubtedly lose this reckless war.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.58,0:10:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it comes down to {\i1}how{\i0} we lose it.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.28,0:10:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Otaka-san, you are absolutely correct.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.49,0:10:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I created the Deep Blue Fleet\Nwith the exact same thought in mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.76,0:10:27.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Deep Blue Fleet.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.96,0:10:33.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This was the fruit of the new school of strategic thought \Nthat Takano Isoroku poured his soul into.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:33.37,0:10:36.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was a trump card that would allow Japan
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.04,0:10:40.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to lose under the best possible terms \Nand avoid a catastrophic disaster.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.37,0:10:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Deep Blue Fleet.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:43.36,0:10:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Powerful, yet eloquent, indeed.\NA fine name.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.44,0:10:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Takano-san, I wish to fight this war fair and square, \Nso that no shame befalls my name.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.30,0:10:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree wholeheartedly.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:53.75,0:10:55.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A few days after this meeting,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.72,0:10:59.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Takano Isoroku was promoted to the position \Nof Commander-In-Chief of the Combined Fleet.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.71,0:11:05.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, the commander's flag was unfurled \Non the battleship Nagato, anchored in Wakanoura. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_battleship_Nagato }
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.60,0:11:15.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then, on September 1st, 1939, in the heart of Europe, \Nthe curtain rose on World War II.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.84,0:11:20.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Nazi Germany unleashed \Nits blitzkrieg against Poland.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.33,0:11:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:25.40,0:11:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Germans have finally done it!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.32,0:11:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You fool! It's nothing to be happy about!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:29.37,0:11:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir! The telegram, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.99,0:11:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.14,0:11:38.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,That devil's made his move at last,\Njust like in my past life, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.17,0:11:42.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,I only wish we could avoid joining hands \Nwith that accursed dictator.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.42,0:11:53.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, just as Takano had feared, \Non September 27th, 1940, the Tripartite Pact was signed.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.92,0:11:57.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, in August of 1941,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.79,0:12:01.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the United States began its own campaign to assert dominance on the Pacific,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.56,0:12:04.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,placing an embargo on all oil exports to Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.54,0:12:06.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In response, the Nanjo Cabinet was formed
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.88,0:12:10.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in October of the same year and adopted a hard-line policy toward the United States. {parody of hideki tojo}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.76,0:12:15.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The cogs of history have begun to turn \Nwith an increasingly grating creak.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:15.72,0:12:18.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,War loomed on the horizon.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.11,0:12:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems it's finally time to spring into action.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.08,0:12:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.38,0:12:33.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,These two great minds resolved not to let \NJapan's future fall into the hands of bigoted fools,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.05,0:12:36.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and devised plans for an elaborate coup d'etat.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.92,0:12:41.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The following day, November 26, \Nthe Takasugi Mobile Air Strike Force {takasugi is parody of https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tamon_Yamaguchi somehow}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.13,0:12:44.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,secretly departed from \NIturup Island's Hitokappu Bay. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kasatka_Bay}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.10,0:12:49.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Starting with Hiei, each vessel in this fleet had been refitted with new, state-of-the-art gas turbine engines. {for this day}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.90,0:12:55.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A mobile task force in more than just name, \Nthey rushed east across the Pacific.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:55.30,0:13:00.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And almost as if on cue, on the very same day, the US would issue
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.11,0:13:03.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,its de facto final ultimatum \Nto Japan in the form of the Hull note. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hull_note}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.08,0:13:10.32,Top,,0,0,0,,Maintain speed, steady as she goes!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.32,0:13:12.24,Top,,0,0,0,,Steady as she goes!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.20,0:13:15.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,We have done all we could. \NAll that's left now is to wait for orders to engage.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.24,0:13:14.72,Top,,0,0,0,,Chikuma, sail in parallel with the flagship!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.90,0:13:21.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On this date, the decision to go to war was made during the morning meeting of the Imperial Council.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.82,0:13:26.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Clouds gathered in the skies over the capital,\Nhiding the sun, and the cold pierced the skin.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.15,0:13:34.52,Thought,,0,0,0,,"The Empire has come to the decision
Dialogue: 10,0:13:34.52,0:13:38.28,Thought,,0,0,0,,to declare war against the US, UK, \Nand the Netherlands in December of this year."
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.28,0:13:40.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,As I thought, history is repeating.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.02,0:13:43.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,But starting tonight, \Nthe course of history shall change!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.56,0:13:55.37,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At 11 p.m., the Cool Breeze Society army \Nof over 20,000 soldiers, led by Otaka,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.56,0:13:52.32,Top,,0,0,0,,First Platoon, forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:52.32,0:13:54.32,Top,,0,0,0,,Second Platoon, forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.32,0:13:56.19,Top,,0,0,0,,Third Platoon, forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:55.37,0:13:58.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,descended upon the moonlit capital\Nin military vehicles.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.50,0:13:59.64,Top,,0,0,0,,Stop! {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.64,0:14:02.18,Top,,0,0,0,,You! Which unit are you with?!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.18,0:14:03.64,Top,,0,0,0,,You bastards!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.06,0:14:12.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the Navy's\NDeep Blue Society also sprung into action,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.09,0:14:15.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,flawlessly executing \Nthe coup d'etat in no time at all.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.54,0:14:13.89,Top,,0,0,0,,Forward!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:15.36,0:14:17.81,Top,,0,0,0,,Second Platoon reporting: all clear!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.36,0:14:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather everyone to be taken into custody, fast!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:20.39,0:14:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir! \NHurry it up!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.58,0:14:32.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The coup forces secured key locations in the imperial capital and martial law was declared.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.18,0:14:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A question for you, \NLieutenant General Otaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.70,0:14:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:42.55,0:14:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Navy Commander-in-Chief Takano \Nis among the signatories of your declaration.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.20,0:14:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean the Navy was also involved?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.92,0:14:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.59,0:14:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal is to address the threat posed by an anticipated \Nwar between Japan and the United States
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.83,0:15:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,by first removing the bigoted military leaders \Nwho had been allowed to run unchecked.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:00.58,0:15:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you plan to reject the Hull Note?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:04.47,0:15:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen well, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.69,0:15:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Hull Note was nothing more\Nthan a calculated scheme,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:09.50,0:15:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,making unreasonable demands \Nfrom our Empire in an attempt to provoke us.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.90,0:15:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That the United States is looking to plunge us into war is the only reasonable explanation for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.40,0:15:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,With that said, gentlemen of the press,\NI would like to ask all of you a great favor.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.16,0:15:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Henceforth, we promise not to obstruct \Nyour press-related activities.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.32,0:15:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In return, we ask that you inform the public \Nof our intentions with no falsehood or ambiguity.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.88,0:15:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean to say that you \Nwill abolish censorship?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.16,0:15:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.56,0:15:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This interview will now conclude.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.06,0:15:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please, one more question!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.34,0:15:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.12,0:15:46.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Otaka's straightforward arguments \Nand resolute policies
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.40,0:15:48.96,Top,,0,0,0,,Extra, extra! Extra!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.92,0:15:50.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,were not directed only \Nat the general public of Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.18,0:15:55.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Along with informing the White House\Nof the establishement of a new government,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.52,0:16:00.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Otaka, now Prime Minister, also gave them a firm response regarding the Hull note.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.43,0:16:06.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That response being, that the withdrawal of the Japanese Empire from China as requested by the Hull note
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.16,0:16:11.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would only be carried out following the total withdrawal of US, UK, and Dutch forces from all parts of Asia.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.58,0:16:13.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the event that this request could not be granted,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.97,0:16:21.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Empire of Japan would declare war against \Nthe US, UK, and the Netherlands to liberate all of Asia.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:21.45,0:16:28.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In addition, the deadline for response was specified to be midnight on December 8th, Japan time.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.94,0:16:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Those impertinent Japs! \NThreatening war so brazenly?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:32.54,0:16:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmph! They're gonna attack us over \Ntens of thousands of miles of the Pacific?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.88,0:16:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bluff. It's obviously a bluff!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.73,0:16:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just nonsense. \NLet's see them try.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.77,0:16:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What can they even do?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.94,0:16:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... Maybe, just maybe, this Otaka might be \Na more problematic opponent than we imagined...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:53.40,0:16:56.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the Takasugi \NMobile Air Strike Force
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.62,0:17:02.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,rushed eastward over the turbulent North Pacific, \Nmaintaining total radio silence.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.49,0:17:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander!\N"Climb Mount Niitaka, 1208!" {code to commence attack on PH}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:08.94,0:17:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.40,0:17:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Comms Officer! \NRelay it to the fleet!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.60,0:17:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.37,0:17:15.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Climb Mount Niitaka."
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.43,0:17:19.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The long-awaited telegram, \Nspecifying the time and date of engagement.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.27,0:17:25.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the event that there was no response from the\NUS government by midnight of December 8th, 1941,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.58,0:17:30.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,this coded message ordered the Takasugi\NMobile Air Strike Force to launch their attack.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:35.10,0:17:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely enough, the US never replied, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.48,0:17:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's less than two hours left until the deadline.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:43.13,0:17:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine that our ambassador in D.C.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.80,0:17:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is making doubly sure by delivering the final statement right about now. {dunno what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.56,0:17:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, the surprise attack's grievances \Nfrom our previous life have been averted. {think he means "before, we struck before the declaration was delivered, now we'll do it properly"}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.87,0:17:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.97,0:17:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We've taken a brave first step
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.78,0:17:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,towards an honorable defeat at the hands \Nof the great power known as America.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.18,0:18:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The deadline proposed by our Empire \Nto the United States of America shall expire as of...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.82,0:18:09.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The news of this matter-of-fact declaration of war
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.69,0:18:13.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,made waves throughout the world, \Nnot limited only to the Americas.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.49,0:18:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Empire has been deeply concerned
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.00,0:18:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,by the miserable conditions of non-white peoples around the world for centuries.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.74,0:18:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus we, the people of Japan,\Nshall rise to action with all our might.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:28.56,0:18:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What nonsense is this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.06,0:18:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They're airing the same thing as their ambassador's declaration all over South America!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.96,0:18:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also being aired in India,\Nthe Middle East, Africa, and the like.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.03,0:18:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't do something,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.75,0:18:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the flames of national independence \Nmay break out all over the world, Mr. President!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.58,0:18:49.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's almost as if they're casting Japan as the champion of justice, while relegating us to the role of villains!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.73,0:18:58.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so, the Takasugi Mobile Strike Force infiltrated\Nthe waters 230 nautical miles north of Oahu, Hawaii,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.40,0:19:01.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,already having made\Nall preparations to be deployed.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.85,0:19:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All aircraft, prepare for take-off!\NAll aircraft, prepare for take-off!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.37,0:19:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Begin take-off!\NBegin take-off!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.14,0:19:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's done a great job \Ntaking off at night like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.90,0:19:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all the fruits of our training, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.38,0:19:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.09,0:19:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The latest model, \Nthe Seidens, is also among them. {fictional plane, developed by deep blue society; https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%98%9F%E9%9B%BB_%28%E7%B4%BA%E7%A2%A7%E3%81%AE%E8%89%A6%E9%9A%8A%29}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.13,0:20:03.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Seiden: recon aircraft, \Nboasting excellent navigation capabilities,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:03.94,0:20:06.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that were not available in the previous world's war.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.81,0:20:09.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Although only the first generation,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:09.34,0:20:13.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,it was a cutting-edge electronic recon aircraft, \Nfully outfitted with high-speed computers.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:14.98,0:20:19.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Seidens, as recon, could lead \Ntheir fellow attack aircraft to the target flawlessly.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.08,0:20:24.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The time was 9:45 p.m.\Non December 7th, Japan time.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:27.54,0:20:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All aircraft of the first attack wave have taken off!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.83,0:20:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A total of 188 units, including bombers!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.06,0:20:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The deadline will expire shortly.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.00,0:20:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.58,0:20:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, the deadline has passed.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:54.40,0:20:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finally time.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.32,0:20:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:03.40,0:21:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The waters around Hawaii \Nare looking clear so far!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.16,0:21:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Maintain course!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:01.44,0:22:06.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The goal of the first attack wave was \Nto decimate the US Army's air power on Hawaii.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.29,0:22:09.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Each of the airbases on Oahu\Nsustained catastrophic damage,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:09.93,0:22:14.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,giving the Takasugi Mobile Air Strike Force\Ncomplete air superiority.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:28.33,0:22:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Bastards!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:33.22,0:22:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there really no warships in sight?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:35.06,0:22:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sir! I can't spot any!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:36.76,0:22:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single one, though?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:38.36,0:22:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't sound plausible.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:39.82,0:22:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Spotted one!\NA capital ship, all on its own!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:43.53,0:22:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Copy that!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:47.92,0:22:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Maintain course, straight ahead!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:49.50,0:22:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Maintaining course!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:52.12,0:22:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Away!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:57.14,0:22:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that? A torpedo?!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:07.45,0:23:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Direct hit!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:08.35,0:23:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Message to flagship! \NEnemy capital ship hit—large fire has broken out!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:18.20,0:23:20.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A few hours prior,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:20.03,0:23:26.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,immediately following the first wave, Takasugi had ordered the launch of a second attack wave.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:26.51,0:23:29.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They were to arrive 30 minutes\Nafter the first attack wave.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:33.38,0:23:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What a sight!\NThe enemy must be in shambles!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.18,0:23:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up! We can't afford to hit \Ntheir fuel depots, no matter what! {lit: not even by mistake}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.26,0:23:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.45,0:23:43.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Preserving the fuel reserves intact
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.14,0:23:48.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was one of the key points \Nof Takano's plan for conquest of Hawaii.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:48.36,0:23:51.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The strategic significance of this \Nwill be explained in due time,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:51.43,0:23:54.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but in any case, like a flock of birds of prey, \Nthe second attack wave
Dialogue: 10,0:23:54.97,0:23:58.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,descended upon Pearl Harbor's \Ndefensive installations.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.67,0:24:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire! Fire! Bring them down!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.17,0:24:06.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Despite having lost control of the air, the American garrison fought back fiercely with that Yankee Spirit,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:06.48,0:24:10.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but alas, the outcome of this battle \Nwas decided before it had even begun.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:18.52,0:24:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Number 25, prepare to drop!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:20.69,0:24:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep her steady!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:32.46,0:24:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oho! Still got some fight left in them!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:41.15,0:24:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yahooo!}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:53.39,0:24:58.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The progress and successes were relayed \Nminutely to Commander Takasugi.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:00.27,0:25:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, as we expected, \Nthe enemy's main force wasn't at Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:04.67,0:25:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly as planned.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:59.36,0:25:02.50,Top,,0,0,0,,The first attack squad will be returning momentarily.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:02.50,0:25:05.08,Top,,0,0,0,,All hands on deck; prepare for landings!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:06.31,0:25:10.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With recommendations from Takano and Otaka, \Nwho were taught by the experiences of their past lives,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:10.98,0:25:17.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Information Bureau was established, greatly bolstering Japan's intelligence-gathering capabilities.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:18.08,0:25:23.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the main force of the American \NPacific Fleet under the command of Admiral Kimmel,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:23.39,0:25:26.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was sailing south towards the Marianas, \Ngeared for battle,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:26.13,0:25:30.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,ready to disrupt Japan's southern transport routes, \Nas outlined by the Rainbow-5 plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:32.30,0:25:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! The Japanese launched an air raid on Hawaii?!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:36.14,0:25:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! Let's turn back immediately and counterattack!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:39.71,0:25:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If it comes down to a naval battle, \Nwe have the upper hand!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:42.54,0:25:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it! This is preposterous!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:45.44,0:25:49.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Fleet Commander Kimmel was at a loss for words.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:49.18,0:25:54.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,If the American Navy ever had a chance to strike a counterblow, this was it.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:54.14,0:26:00.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, Kimmel was too cautious. He was unable to estimate just how strong Takasugi's fleet was.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:00.06,0:26:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:01.44,0:26:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! It wouldn't be too late to follow up\Nafter we rendezvous with Halsey!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:05.10,0:26:08.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the bold Vice Admiral "Bull" Halsey
Dialogue: 10,0:26:08.50,0:26:13.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was in a rush to return, being 120 nautical miles west of Oahu upon receiving the emergency call. {just says "he was in a rush" doesn't tell to do what so idk}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:17.02,0:26:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What is there to hesitate about?!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:19.08,0:26:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to turn back immediately\Nand crush that Japanese fleet!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:23.08,0:26:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We will rendezvous with you ASAP.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:24.94,0:26:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our perfect chance to make those\Nunderhanded Japs drink some Pacific seawater!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:29.98,0:26:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, understood. Once we've regrouped\Nwith the Lexington, we'll make our way back.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:35.06,0:26:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Again with that!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:37.13,0:26:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy air fleet should all be absent right now! \NGo after them immedia—
Dialogue: 10,0:26:40.66,0:26:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, something just came in.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:44.17,0:26:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Our plane just made contact\Nwith an enemy recon plane!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:46.96,0:26:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! Where?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:48.57,0:26:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,140 miles to the west of Oahu!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.91,0:26:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust they shot it down?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:53.64,0:26:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it says the thing was as fast \Nas the devil himself. It ran northwest.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.18,0:26:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Northwest?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.95,0:27:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like lady luck blessed me this time, not you.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:01.05,0:27:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The mark's closer to my location.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:02.98,0:27:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm heading straight north \Ninto Kauai Channel to intercept them!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:05.94,0:27:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on! You're going to pursue it \Non a mere guess alone?!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.66,0:27:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait until we rendezvous!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:10.38,0:27:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Whichever side finds the other first wins here! \NAnd I'll put my bets on me!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:14.76,0:27:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Bob, send out reconnaissance planes \Nto Oahu's coastal waters.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:17.77,0:27:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:18.70,0:27:20.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Halsey's foolhardiness would cost him dearly. {/backfired}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:20.97,0:27:27.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This long-range communication was picked up \Nby two new Japanese Seiden recon planes,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:27.41,0:27:32.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,which were then able to triangulate \Nthe exact locations of both enemy fleets.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:36.29,0:27:39.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And the carrier fleet\Nunder Halesey's command is here.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:39.34,0:27:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, intelligence is the key to victory.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:42.90,0:27:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:44.28,0:27:48.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,Unless that man is dispatched of, \Nwe can't move onto the next phase of our plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:48.25,0:27:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The first attack wave is about to land!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:50.44,0:27:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they're back?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:01.45,0:28:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work out there!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:04.42,0:28:06.64,Top,,0,0,0,,Refuel and rearm, on the double!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:08.42,0:28:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry it up! Our next target is waiting!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:10.49,0:28:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like it's gonna be a carrier!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:15.69,0:28:20.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At the start of the war, the US Pacific Fleet \Nhad three aircraft carriers.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:20.48,0:28:23.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Along with the occupation of Hawaii, \Nthe destruction of these carriers
Dialogue: 10,0:28:23.85,0:28:26.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was the main objective of the day.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:27.92,0:28:34.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Without a minute to rest, the first attack squad\Nrefueled, rearmed, and sortied once again.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:37.78,0:28:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When you do it, \Nyou do it thoroughly and resolutely.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:41.05,0:28:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what Admiral Takano is truly made of, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:43.79,0:28:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:45.26,0:28:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he is the enemy,\NI do feel a tad bit sorry for Halsey.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:49.73,0:28:55.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Commander-in-Chief Takasugi's enigmatic monologue \Nwould make sense a few minutes later.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:57.57,0:28:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! Those imbeciles from the Army?!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:59.84,0:29:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care! Shoot back without hesitation\Nat everyone who dares fire at us, friend or foe!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:05.54,0:29:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! Everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:05.21,0:29:09.82,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,After hearing that his ship-borne recon plane \Nwas shot down by Oahu's air defenses,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:09.82,0:29:12.52,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,the gung-ho Halsey was sent into a fit of rage.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:13.44,0:29:17.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Unaware of their doom creeping towards them,\NHalsey's Carrier Task Force,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:17.88,0:29:21.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,consisting of one aircraft carrier, \Nthree heavy cruisers, and nine destroyers,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:21.68,0:29:24.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,suddenly came under torpedo fire.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:32.16,0:29:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happening?!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:33.54,0:29:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Torpedoes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:34.44,0:29:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:38.11,0:29:42.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It is hardly surprising that the fleet failed \Nto spot these torpedoes, for they sneaked in
Dialogue: 10,0:29:42.65,0:29:47.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,from a distance of three kilometers at a speed \Nof thirty-six knots, without leaving so much as a trace.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:09.84,0:30:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay calm! All compartments, damage report!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:12.94,0:30:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hits on starboard, three direct hits on the hull! {???? can't hear shit except for "three shots" even though we only see two columns}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:15.88,0:30:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship's taking on water! {?????? even more can't hear shit, not a single word}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:28.73,0:30:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sinking! Run! {???? guess}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:31.13,0:30:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Where do you think you're going?! \NGet back here!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:33.92,0:30:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no order to abandon ship!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:36.37,0:30:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Return fire! Beat those bastards down!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:40.71,0:30:48.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Without ever knowing the real cause of his defeat,\NHalsey met his fate alongside his ship, the Enterprise.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:51.18,0:30:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Halsey's been killed in action?!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:53.27,0:30:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His entire fleet, along with \Nthe USS Enterprise, has been sunk...
Dialogue: 10,0:30:58.54,0:31:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! A report has just arrived—
Dialogue: 10,0:31:00.56,0:31:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the aircraft carrier Lexington \Nhas been sunk in the waters southeast of Midway!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:05.01,0:31:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! What is the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:07.18,0:31:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a torpedo attack...
Dialogue: 10,0:31:08.83,0:31:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it a submarine?!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:10.20,0:31:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The details are unclear, but according to a report \Nfrom one of the destroyer escorts,
Dialogue: 10,0:31:14.44,0:31:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they were hit by five torpedoes at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:16.98,0:31:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The ship's hull split into three \Nand it sunk instantly!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:19.95,0:31:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:21.25,0:31:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impossible...
Dialogue: 10,0:31:22.91,0:31:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way five torpedoes \Nstruck a single ship all at once, is there?!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:26.15,0:31:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least they've spotted the attacker, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:28.82,0:31:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sir...
Dialogue: 10,0:31:30.48,0:31:32.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kimmel's disbelief was justified.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:32.92,0:31:38.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The destroyers, circling around the capital ships, \Nwere supposed to detect any incoming submarine attack.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:38.93,0:31:44.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The fact that they penetrated the tight screen \Nso easily while remaining hidden
Dialogue: 10,0:31:44.10,0:31:48.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,showed just how formidable a force \Nthe Deep Blue Fleet could be.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:48.62,0:31:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't suppose the Japanese \Nmight have developed
Dialogue: 10,0:31:51.78,0:31:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a new kind of weapon \Nwe don't yet understand, do you?
Dialogue: 10,0:31:55.85,0:31:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Knock it off with those foolish delusions!
Dialogue: 10,0:31:58.95,0:32:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize, sir.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:01.98,0:32:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But still...
Dialogue: 10,0:32:03.42,0:32:07.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This unexpected and rapid chain of events\Nhad left Kimmel at a loss.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:07.24,0:32:12.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, \NTakasugi's fleet detached five carriers—
Dialogue: 10,0:32:12.80,0:32:18.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Zuikaku, Shokaku, Kaga, Soryu, and Hiryu—\Ntogether with transports and a destroyer escort,
Dialogue: 10,0:32:18.10,0:32:21.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in order to lure Kimmel's main force into battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:21.82,0:32:25.61,Top,,0,0,0,,The aircraft carrier Lexington has been torpedoed and sunk while en route to Midway!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:25.61,0:32:28.01,Top,,0,0,0,,That is all for this announcement! {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:28.01,0:32:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like the Deep Blue Fleet\Nhas finally made its move.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:31.32,0:32:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:32.78,0:32:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy are in such shambles\N that they're using clear text to communicate.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:36.36,0:32:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No code at all?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:37.86,0:32:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for waiting! \NChow for the front line is here!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:40.61,0:32:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, please have some!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:42.30,0:32:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oho, isn't that red rice?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:44.10,0:32:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In celebration of our victory, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:46.03,0:32:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ey, hands off! \NCommander gets the first one!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:48.90,0:32:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oho... these look delicious.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:50.56,0:32:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't find anything better in this world!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:51.87,0:32:54.07,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Is that so? Let's see here...
Dialogue: 10,0:32:58.28,0:32:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, they're the best in the world!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:59.96,0:33:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:00.95,0:33:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let it go to your head, cook!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:08.44,0:33:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander, are we setting the bait for our enemy?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:11.08,0:33:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:12.49,0:33:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, conventional doctrine dictates
Dialogue: 10,0:33:15.16,0:33:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that we pull those ships back \Nand avoid being drawn into a naval battle... {lit: there's also meaning in ... - think he means they're going against the conventional wisdom with this}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:18.93,0:33:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then... Navigation Officer!\NHave the fleet set sail for Oahu Island!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:24.00,0:33:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:28.37,0:33:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy fleet spotted, heading southward!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:30.73,0:33:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Fleet composition is: two battleships, one carrier,\Ntwo heavy cruisers and three destroyers!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:35.70,0:33:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Over and out!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:42.32,0:33:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one aircraft carrier?!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:44.50,0:33:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We have yet to locate any other carriers.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:47.86,0:33:49.64,Thought,,0,0,0,,But that can't be right...
Dialogue: 10,0:33:49.64,0:33:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! Let's do this!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:51.78,0:33:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, we ought to crush \Nany enemy we can find. {lit: first, crush the enemy before our eyes}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:55.23,0:33:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The air fleet of a single carrier \Nis no scarier than a bunch of flies!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:00.27,0:34:02.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Indeed, considering the proportion of forces,
Dialogue: 10,0:34:02.41,0:34:05.46,Thought,,0,0,0,,if we engage them in an artillery battle, \Nwe can pulverize them at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:05.46,0:34:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are they?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:06.61,0:34:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir! Approximately 70 nautical miles \Nnortheast of Oahu!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:10.34,0:34:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Judging by their course, don't they seem to be heading towards Pearl Harbor?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:15.10,0:34:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they be?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:16.20,0:34:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pearl Harbor has already been destroyed \Nby those air raids, has it not?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:21.33,0:34:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite. There are still four and a half million barrels worth of fuel oil left intact at fuel depots there.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:26.73,0:34:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If they destroyed it, our fleet would be unable \Nto operate in the Pacific for at least six months.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:32.80,0:34:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be it!\NSo that's what they're after!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:36.12,0:34:39.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kimmel had resolved to act \Nupon those two considerations.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:39.64,0:34:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Order the entire fleet \Nto proceed at full speed!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:42.71,0:34:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The honor of The United States Navy is at stake! \NWe're going to wipe out the Japanese fleet!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:50.39,0:34:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy fleet has been spotted by local fishermen!\NThey're heading towards Kauai Channel! {yep, that's really what he's saying}
Dialogue: 10,0:34:54.98,0:34:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Kauai Channel?!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:58.26,0:35:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Kauai Channel...
Dialogue: 10,0:35:00.67,0:35:06.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In Kimmel's mind, a sudden thought flashed \Nof the enemy ships that had annihilated Halsey's fleet.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:06.44,0:35:10.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, a word from his officers\Nreassured the anxious admiral.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:11.38,0:35:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! Our circular combat formation is perfect!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:14.91,0:35:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll take more than \Nwhat they've got to break through it!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:17.45,0:35:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! Let's avenge Halsey's fleet!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:20.82,0:35:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:21.65,0:35:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Set a course straight for Kauai Channel! \NWe'll intercept the enemy there!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:26.46,0:35:28.83,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,Majestic and powerful,
Dialogue: 10,0:35:28.83,0:35:33.37,Narrtop,,0,0,0,,this was truly an armada that would be worthy \Nof carrying the title of Ruler of the Pacific.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:34.18,0:35:36.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Takasugi's fleet, in contrast...
Dialogue: 10,0:35:38.14,0:35:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Transmission from Seidens!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:39.74,0:35:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Kimmel's fleet has set course for Kauai Channel!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:43.34,0:35:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{Understood!}
Dialogue: 10,0:35:44.52,0:35:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Navigation Officer! \NAre we good with our current speed?
Dialogue: 10,0:35:48.51,0:35:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The success of this operation\Nhinges on our timing, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:51.68,0:35:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's slow down a bit.\NAbout 28 knots should be just right.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:00.72,0:36:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy ships!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:02.76,0:36:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Corporal Quinton!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:04.34,0:36:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They're here! The Japanese fleet!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:09.80,0:36:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Message from Mt. Ka'ala Observation Post:
Dialogue: 10,0:36:11.90,0:36:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy fleet spotted over the horizon,\Nbearing east-northeast!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:15.64,0:36:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They've shown themselves.\NGood, we've made it in time.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:19.08,0:36:23.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Kauai Channel is a channel sandwiched \Nbetween the islands of Oahu and Kauai.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:23.70,0:36:28.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Stretching to around 100 km in width,\N it provides ample space for fleet deployment.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:28.35,0:36:30.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Just a little past 01:40 p.m.,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:30.19,0:36:34.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,a tremendous show of back-and-forth artillery fire \Nbetween capital ships had begun.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:46.60,0:36:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Open fire!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:58.43,0:37:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge! The Imperial Navy \Nis no match for our fleet!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:04.56,0:37:07.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The earsplitting roars \Nand blinding flashes of cannon fire
Dialogue: 10,0:37:07.99,0:37:10.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,had robbed Kimmel of his composure.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:18.77,0:37:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it. I don't understand\Nwhere they get their nerve from. {lit: don't understand their nerve}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:22.47,0:37:27.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even with his own fleet's \Noverwhelming firepower before his eyes,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:27.48,0:37:30.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,an inexplicable premonition \Ngripped Kimmel's heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:30.50,0:37:31.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 10,0:37:35.98,0:37:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Staff Officer, relay this to all ships!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:38.54,0:37:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Maintain this distance \Nand strive for more accurate fire!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:41.83,0:37:45.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Takasugi fleet seemed \Nto be waiting for something to happen,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:45.36,0:37:48.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,fleeing when pursued \Nand giving chase when the enemy withdrew. {meaning they tried to keep the battle going, pin the enemy fleet down with fighting - dunno if that's clear enough from that wording}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:49.10,0:37:50.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And sure enough...
Dialogue: 10,0:37:54.48,0:37:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy aircraft approaching!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:56.08,0:37:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Portside, 30 degrees! \NAltitude, 2000! Distance, 7000!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:59.28,0:38:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:05.92,0:38:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Were we tricked?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:07.98,0:38:13.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A new wave of attack aircraft that should \Nnot have been in the channel swooped in.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:33.78,0:38:36.90,Top,,0,0,0,,Portside, 16 degrees! \NNew enemy fleet spotted!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:39.25,0:38:44.06,Top,,0,0,0,,Five battleships! No, six! Three carriers!\NFour heavy cruisers! And there's still more!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:44.06,0:38:46.69,Top,,0,0,0,,Approaching at high speed\Nwith a vanguard of destroyers!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:48.19,0:38:52.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The newly arrived fleet was the main force \Nof a combined fleet of capital ships
Dialogue: 10,0:38:52.10,0:38:54.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,under the command \Nof Vice Admiral Ryoma Sakamoto.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:55.44,0:39:01.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In accordance with Takano's plans, this fleet\Nhad been covertly heading towards these waters.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:01.06,0:39:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,222)}Takasugi-san, are we late?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:04.56,0:39:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(309,0)}No, your timing is impeccable.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:08.60,0:39:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The fleets are now evenly matched.\NEight of our battleships against eight of theirs.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:12.77,0:39:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, shall we treat them\Nto a bit of shock and awe? {lit: give them a scare}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:20.04,0:39:25.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With no air support to speak of, and sandwiched in the channel between two enemy fleets,
Dialogue: 10,0:39:25.45,0:39:27.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,after some three hours of intense fighting,
Dialogue: 10,0:39:27.80,0:39:32.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the majority of Kimmel's fleet \Nhad been disabled, or worse, sunk.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:32.24,0:39:36.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was at this point \Nthat Kimmel finally realized it...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:43.11,0:39:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:45.37,0:39:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why won't they aim \Nfor our battleships, the main force?!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:49.42,0:39:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no idea what their intentions are.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:51.36,0:39:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All we can say for sure \Nis that we've been left completely exposed.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:55.81,0:39:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:58.20,0:40:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?\NI can't figure out what their plan is!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:01.62,0:40:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do?! Do I hold on \Nto my pride as a soldier and charge in?! {lit: show my soldier's guts}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:04.57,0:40:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be one way to go about it, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:07.36,0:40:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of our ships are out of ammo,\Nand as good as scrap metal at this point.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:11.64,0:40:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you telling me to surrender?\NTo the goddamn Japs?!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:15.61,0:40:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse! I absolutely refuse!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:17.26,0:40:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral! The sun will set soon!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:19.42,0:40:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make our escape under the cover of darkness!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:21.62,0:40:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:22.72,0:40:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, surviving to fight another day \Nis an option as well, but... {not sure what he says, but I hear this, not "cutting our losses and retreating" from the og tl}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:26.52,0:40:31.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kimmel was yet again\Ngripped by a strange premonition.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:31.06,0:40:35.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He felt as though something was hiding right\Nunder his nose, beneath the gold-tinted waves.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:36.27,0:40:39.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Still, he deliberately suppressed that anxiety.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:39.32,0:40:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot let them smear \Nthe honor of the US Navy!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:43.16,0:40:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Charg—
Dialogue: 10,0:40:51.95,0:40:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Th-The Arizona...
Dialogue: 10,0:40:54.55,0:40:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that how they got the Lexington, too...?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:13.14,0:41:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a torpedo attack...
Dialogue: 10,0:41:14.50,0:41:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did it come from?!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:16.96,0:41:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn't even see a trail!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:19.24,0:41:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It only took three shots to sink her...
Dialogue: 10,0:41:22.30,0:41:26.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This mysterious torpedo attack, \Nwhich no one could see coming,
Dialogue: 10,0:41:26.05,0:41:30.82,Narrator,,0,0,0,,consigned the Arizona and the Oklahoma \Nto the depths in the blink of an eye. {adds "taking a moment's break" but idk what this is about, probably means "giving kimmel a moment to think" but I don't think it's needed}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:30.82,0:41:34.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Clearly, it was urging Kimmel \Nto make a very specific decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:35.41,0:41:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there nothing I can do anymore but surrender?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:39.32,0:41:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse! I absolutely...
Dialogue: 10,0:41:40.96,0:41:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral...
Dialogue: 10,0:41:42.54,0:41:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no other choice left.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:44.32,0:41:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, the lives of the crew are irreplaceable.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:49.44,0:41:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 10,0:41:50.42,0:41:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Admiral!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:55.18,0:41:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. \NLet us surrender.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:57.65,0:42:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the rest of our fleet, whatever remains, \Nknow that we will raise the white flag.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:02.32,0:42:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:03.86,0:42:06.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Around the time the artillery battle \Nat Kauai Channel had ended,
Dialogue: 10,0:42:06.79,0:42:11.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,a landing force, supported by a destroyer escort, \Noccupied all of the Hawaiian archipelago.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:11.53,0:42:15.83,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With this, Project 1208 had reached its final stage.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:17.25,0:42:19.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Landing units, numbering around 7,000 troops,
Dialogue: 10,0:42:19.40,0:42:23.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,easily eliminated what little resistance remained \Nand succeeded in occupying
Dialogue: 10,0:42:23.44,0:42:26.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the entirety of Pearl Harbor's naval facilities.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:26.19,0:42:27.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It should go without saying
Dialogue: 10,0:42:27.98,0:42:31.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that the true goal of this operation \Nwas securing the 4.5 million barrels of fuel.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:36.12,0:42:37.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Climb Mount Niitaka."
Dialogue: 10,0:42:37.99,0:42:42.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The battle that started the Pacific War, \Ntriggered by that code phrase{ "1208"} on December 8th had,
Dialogue: 10,0:42:42.43,0:42:47.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,just like it did in the previous world, \Nended in a decisive victory for the Empire of Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:47.13,0:42:53.08,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However, there was a dramatic difference \Nin the strategic advantage gained from this victory.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:55.00,0:43:01.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Thus, in preparation for this declaration of war, \Nthe Japanese Navy had succeeded in creating a fleet
Dialogue: 10,0:43:01.21,0:43:04.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of giant submarines \Nconcealed deep beneath the blue waves.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:08.34,0:43:11.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was dubbed the {\i1}Deep Blue Fleet{\i0}.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:11.58,0:43:18.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was the trump card that Japan needed \Nin this unwinnable war,
Dialogue: 10,0:43:18.03,0:43:20.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,allowing it to lose on favorable terms.
